net.objectzoo.events.impl

Class Event2Distributor<T1,T2>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.objectzoo.events.impl.Event2Distributor<T1,T2>
  • Type Parameters:
    T1 - The type of the first information parameter the event provides
    T2 - The type of the second information parameter the event provides
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.function.BiConsumer<T1,T2>, Action2<T1,T2>, Event2<T1,T2>, Event2Delegate<T1,T2>

    public class Event2Distributor<T1,T2>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Event2Delegate<T1,T2>
    The Event2Distributor is a Event2Delegate implementation allows that event distribution to multiple subscribers. It is a helper class that encapsulates all the logic required to provide events in other classes. Subscriber invocations are performed in the order of subscription.

    tilmann
